                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14456109" author="hboutemy" created="Fri, 27 Jun 2014 15:36:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;can you point to a sample output that shows the issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456187" author="jeversmann" created="Mon, 30 Jun 2014 20:41:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a screenshot I took of a malformed stack trace.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456291" author="agudian" created="Sat, 27 Sep 2014 13:24:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m unsure about merging the PR, as I think that a fix should rather be done in the sink implementation. Or was that done already? Is there a dependency that we need to update for the Surefire-Report plugin?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Herve, what do you think is the problem here?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456401" author="hboutemy" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 00:05:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;since the actual Surefire code contains &quot;sink.lineBreak();&quot;, ie the HTML output should contain a newline and the &amp;lt;pre&amp;gt; should display it in a browser, I&apos;m really skeptical about the fix&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I really need a sample output to study what is not working as expected (and by &quot;output&quot;, I mean the HTML content to really study it)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Andreas, did you observe such an issue in one of your reports?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456440" author="ulli" created="Thu, 11 Dec 2014 15:33:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the Surefire site report does not show newlines for stacktraces &lt;b&gt;and&lt;/b&gt; assertion messages. Here is an example project (branch assignments5):  &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/uhafner/karatest/tree/assignments5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/uhafner/karatest/tree/assignments5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
When you run &lt;tt&gt;mvn clean test -Dmaven.test.failure.ignore=true site&lt;/tt&gt; then the Surefire report shows the assertion message in a single line. Should I provide a screenshot or is the project sufficient to reproduce?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14525989" author="tibor17" created="Sun, 3 May 2015 20:05:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jeversmann&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jeversmann&quot;&gt;jeversmann&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Can you please retest with `maven-site-plugin:3.4` and doxia 1.4?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14576501" author="tibor17" created="Sun, 7 Jun 2015 23:29:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have reproduced this issue.&lt;br/&gt;
The issue appears with error/assertion message which contains several lines \n.&lt;br/&gt;
The fix in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/pull/41&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/pull/41&lt;/a&gt; does not solve this issue because the loop in SurefireReportGenerator.javaL534 iterates just once.&lt;br/&gt;
I would expect that the loop would iterate over all lines expanding the width of the table in Detail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the Test Cases table contains a row with&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;+ [ Detail ]&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
error message&lt;br/&gt;
and detail if click on it&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would expect short error message like the first line from multiple lines,&lt;br/&gt;
and detail would be properly formatted message with multiple lines.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most probably this is really not an issue of Doxia but surefire.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14576510" author="tibor17" created="Sun, 7 Jun 2015 23:55:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems I found the issue in surefire, TestSuiteXmlParser.parseCause(TestSuiteXmlParser.java:L311)&lt;br/&gt;
My test method is called &quot;t&quot; and the point of parseCause() is to find the name of method in the error message and print just only that particular line, but the error message does not need to contain the name of method - I mean does not make sense to filter like this. I don&apos;t know why it was coded like this and I have no idea what side effect will be after removing the filer from parseCause().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579746" author="tibor17" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 23:27:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;commit	8a2cd06aae749ed63d62541842b58f8983c71a0b&lt;br/&gt;
commit	989479ea8451d11bdbe3e252892466574bcdf467&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17994489" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:22:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1574&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1574&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
